// Querying uses plain JS methods (in MongoDB)


// Advantages
- Schemaless - easy to prototype
- Faster than RDBMS
- Good for domains where schema for an entity cannot be well-defined
- It is scalable - easy to cluster, easy to shard MongoDB data

// Disadvantages
- Schemaless - data integrity (involves data duplication)
- No Transactions (no rollback) - old version